radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal left basilar atelectasis; tiny hypodensity within hepatic segment VII likely a simple cyst; gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and left kidney are normal; marked dilatation of a fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 11 mm in diameter; 4-mm appendicolith within the mid appendix; periappendiceal fat stranding without fluid collection or perforation; small lymph nodes adjacent to the cecum do not meet size criteria; small quantity of free fluid in the pelvis; no pathologically enlarged pelvic lymph nodes seen; 6-mm sclerotic focus in the right femoral neck likely a bone island.
